                <head>No. 262.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hoppin</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-11-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 10, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Hoppin telegraphs to Mr. Frelinghuysen that officer of police reports
                    information given in Donegal by O’Donnell’s family that his father’s name was
                    Michael; that the father lived in Pennsylvania while in America, being in
                    Philadelphia and along the banks of the Delaware chiefly; that the father was
                    never a naturalized citizen, and that he died some eighteen years ago.</p>
            </div>
